  "text": "Glycosylation is critical for a wide range of biological processes, including cell attachment to the extracellular matrix and proteinligand interactions in the cell. It has been reported that about twothird entries of proteins in SWISS-PROT are glycosylated that may be either N-linked carbohydrate units, O-linked or both N-and Olinked [CITATION_1] . In the present study, it is found that proteins of the drug target dataset used are either potential glycosylated or nonglycosylated. It indicated that these proteins are not proper glycoproteins.",
